      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Some snow fell on Tuesday in some regions. <br/> The surface of the snowpack will soften during the day. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack below approximately 3000 m. <br/> Steep west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2500 m: Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack. <br/> Below approximately 2000 m from a snow sport perspective, in most cases insufficient snow is lying. <br/>"
      },
